{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Digital Thermometer (C / Embedded Systems)"},"html":"<h2>Digital Thermometer (C / Embedded Systems)</h2>\n<h4><em>Mar 2018 - May 2018 | San Diego State University</em></h4>\n<h5>A digital thermometer using a PIC16F18324 microcontroller.</h5>\n<hr>\n<p><strong><em>Senior Design A Project</em></strong> <br/>\n▪ Designed a digital thermometer that displays temperature on a dual 7-segment display. <br/>\n▪ Used Mentor Graphics Design Capture to design the PCB board.<br/>\n▪ Worked with a PIC16F18324 Microcontroller.<br/>\n▪ Utilized SPI communication to control the Display Driver from the Microcontroller.<br/></p>\n<hr>\n<p>**Block Diagram - Figure 1** <br/><>\n![block_diagram](./dt_block_diagram.png)\n<p><strong>Schematic - Figure 2</strong> <br/>\n<span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 684px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.57894736842105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"schematic\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/42550e38f6bd2c96b7d1ac7f9450b778/238ba/dt_schematic.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/42550e38f6bd2c96b7d1ac7f9450b778/f10b8/dt_schematic.png 238w,\n/static/42550e38f6bd2c96b7d1ac7f9450b778/aff45/dt_schematic.png 475w,\n/static/42550e38f6bd2c96b7d1ac7f9450b778/238ba/dt_schematic.png 684w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 684px) 100vw, 684px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><strong>PCB - Figure 3</strong> <br/>\n<span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; 